al text model (Agentic), matching the minimum level.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0,"Agentic":0.85,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"Post passing both image and text checks is published, not held or silently dropped","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Once model outputs (both 'safe') are available, the routing decision is deterministic. The failure is in the application logic: does the code correctly route to publish when both models pass? This is a logic bug, not a model accuracy issue. We can mock both models to return 'safe' and test the pipeline routing, catching publish-path failures without needing the real models.","test_description":"Mock both the vision and text models to return 'safe' classifications, submit a post through the moderation pipeline, and verify it appears in the published queue with correct metadata, not in hold or drop queues.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test mocks both models (Integration), matching the minimum level for testing routing logic.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"Full moderation pipeline (image check, text check, publish) completes within 5 seconds","minimum_level":"Workflow","justification":"Latency is measurable only with real API calls. Mocking both models would hide real network latency and AI model inference time, making the test artificially fast. The failure is 'real vision model + real text model + publish takes > 5 seconds'. This requires multiple agentic steps (vision→text→publish) executed sequentially in the real environment.","test_description":"Submit a real image and text post to the production moderation pipeline with both real vision and text model APIs enabled, measure elapsed time from submission to publication, and assert total latency is less than 5 seconds. Run multiple times to capture realistic variance.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test calls both real models sequentially and measures end-to-end latency (Workflow level), matching the minimum needed to catch real-world timing failures.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0,"Integration":0.1,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.2,"Workflow":0.55}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When vision model is unavailable, image posts are queued for retry rather than auto-approved","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure is in the application's error-handling logic, not in the network layer or HTTP client resilience. Once we reliably simulate the vision model being unavailable (via exception mocking), the response path is deterministic. We can verify the queueing logic without needing a real unavailable API.","test_description":"Mock the vision model client to raise a connection timeout error, submit an image post to the pipeline, and verify the post is stored in a retry queue with retry metadata (attempt count, next retry time), not auto-approved to publication.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test mocks vision model error (Integration), matching the minimum level for error-handling logic.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.1,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.15,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"Moderation decision is consistent when the same image is submitted multiple times within a short window","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Real vision models may be non-deterministic on borderline images (floating-point precision, batch effects, GPU memory state). Mocking the model to return the same result twice hides the critical question: does the system cache decisions, or does it rely on lucky model consistency? We need the real model to test whether the system handles non-determinism via caching or fails when the model's second call returns a different confidence/classification.","test_description":"Submit the same borderline image twice in quick succession (within the short window), invoking the real vision model both times, and verify both submissions receive identical moderation decisions (either both flagged or both published). If decision differs, verify it was due to documented model variance, not system bugs.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Test calls real vision model twice (Agentic), matching the minimum level to expose model non-determinism or caching logic failures.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.1,"Agentic":0.6,"Workflow":0.05}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13496,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13496},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ea2209f1-69a7-4101-a903-7fc58fbcc39b","uuid":"9bef04ee-f61a-40e1-894d-d436c942f627"}
